  "title": "Pricing and Billing System Analyst",
  "description": "<p>We are hiring Pricing and Billing System Analyst with below requirements;<br /><strong>Required Skills & Experience</strong></p><ul><li>Requirements Analysis & Elicitation – Prepare comprehensive Business Requirements Documents (BRDs) focused on pricing models, billing structures, and client invoicing mechanisms.</li><li>Define detailed functional specifications based on business requirements or user stories related to pricing and billing workflows.</li><li>Analyze and propose “to-be” business and operational processes for pricing and billing, perform impact assessments and estimations.</li><li>Collaborate with Technology teams to ensure proposed solutions align with business needs and regulatory requirements.</li><li>Monitor and manage risks/issues related to scope creep and requirement changes.</li><li>Translate business requirements into test scenarios and support User Acceptance Testing (UAT).</li><li>Provide “Train-the-Trainer” sessions on pricing and billing enhancements.</li><li>Maintain subject matter expertise in pricing strategies, billing systems, and corporate banking products.</li><li>Clarify test findings escalated by QA teams and classify them as defects or change requests.</li><li>Perform impact assessments and estimations for project change requests.</li><li>Ensure compliance with financial services policies, procedures, and industry practices related to billing and pricing.</li></ul><p><strong>Nice to Have:</strong></p><ul><li>Experience in designing user journeys for pricing and billing features on digital banking channels.</li><li>Knowledge of competitor offerings in pricing and billing.</li><li>Exposure to API, H2H, and SWIFT-based billing integrations</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
